<subSubSection id="C31A65385E3CFFF7FF1C34BDFDDAFA0C" pageId="11" pageNumber="26" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BBF36B35E3CFFF7FF1C34BDFDDAFA0C" blockId="11.[129,778,1396,2028]" pageId="11" pageNumber="26">
À propos de ces deux taxons endémiques de 
<collectingCountry id="F31776235E3CFFF7FDD434BAFD57FA2C" box="[588,714,1459,1485]" name="Madagascar" pageId="11" pageNumber="26">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
, deux changements nomenclaturaux s’imposent:
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C31A65385E3CFFF7FF1C34FAFB1DFA6F" pageId="11" pageNumber="26" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BBF36B35E3CFFF7FF1C34FAFA1FFC0E" blockId="11.[129,778,1396,2028]" lastBlockId="11.[810,1457,949,1422]" pageId="11" pageNumber="26">
<emphasis id="B974EAA15E3CFFF7FF1C34FAFED3F9EC" box="[132,334,1523,1549]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="26">
– 
<taxonomicName id="4C004D305E3CFFF7FF0434FAFED3F9EC" box="[156,334,1523,1549]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Pteridaceae" genus="Pteris" kingdom="Plantae" order="Polypodiales" pageId="11" pageNumber="26" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lanceifolia">Pteris lanceifolia</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
possède un limbe 1-penné; les pennes proximales ne sont pas décroissantes et ne possèdent pas de ramifications basiscopiques; les nervures sont anastomosées. La variété-type a des pennes entières; la variété 
<taxonomicName id="4C004D305E3CFFF7FD09375BFD68F98D" authorityName="Baker" authorityYear="1876" box="[657,757,1618,1644]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Pteridaceae" genus="Pteris" kingdom="Plantae" order="Polypodiales" pageId="11" pageNumber="26" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="platyodon">
<emphasis id="B974EAA15E3CFFF7FD09375BFD68F98D" box="[657,757,1618,1644]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="26">platyodon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
a des pennes plus ou moins profondément et irrégulièrement lobées (Christensen 1932; Tardieu-Blot 1958). Or, l’examen des nombreux spécimens déposés à P et les observations de terrain montrent que tous les stades intermédiaires entre ces deux formes de limbe coexistent dans la nature. À titre d’exemple, citons les récoltes 
<emphasis id="B974EAA15E3CFFF7FECB361BFDF4F8CA" box="[339,617,1809,1836]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="26">Perrier de la Bâthie 6080</emphasis>
(P01315448; P01588983) et 
<emphasis id="B974EAA15E3CFFF7FEBD3638FD97F8AA" box="[293,522,1841,1867]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="26">Rakotondrainibe 2692</emphasis>
(P00059889) qui montrent sur le même individu des pennes entières, des pennes sinueuses et des pennes lobées. 
<collectingRegion id="49C4F8515E3CFFF7FE44367BFD9DF86D" box="[476,512,1906,1932]" country="Cameroon" name="East" pageId="11" pageNumber="26">Les</collectingRegion>
pennes fertiles des deux variétés et des formes intermédiaires portent des sporanges normaux qui, lorsqu’ils sont mûrs, laissent échapper de bonnes spores translucides, réniformes. Sans analyses cytologiques, la nature hybride des formes intermédiaires ne peut être retenue. La synonymie entre les deux variétés est donc proposée.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BBF36B35E3CFFF7FCB532FCFB1DFA6F" blockId="11.[810,1457,949,1422]" pageId="11" pageNumber="26">
– À l’inverse de tous les 
<taxonomicName id="4C004D305E3CFFF7FBA232FCFBEEFBEF" box="[1082,1139,1013,1038]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Pteridaceae" genus="Pteris" kingdom="Plantae" order="Polypodiales" pageId="11" pageNumber="26" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B974EAA15E3CFFF7FBA232FCFBEEFBEF" box="[1082,1139,1013,1038]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="26">Pteris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
connus, les spécimens placés sous 
<taxonomicName id="4C004D305E3CFFF7FCC6351CFB9DFBCF" box="[862,1024,1044,1070]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Pteridaceae" genus="Pteris" kingdom="Plantae" order="Polypodiales" pageId="11" pageNumber="26" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lanceifolia">
<emphasis id="B974EAA15E3CFFF7FCC6351CFB9DFBCF" box="[862,1024,1044,1070]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="26">Pteris lanceifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(variété 
<taxonomicName id="4C004D305E3CFFF7FBCB351DFB29FBCF" authorityName="Baker" authorityYear="1876" box="[1107,1204,1044,1070]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Pteridaceae" genus="Pteris" kingdom="Plantae" order="Polypodiales" pageId="11" pageNumber="26" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="platyodon">
<emphasis id="B974EAA15E3CFFF7FBCB351DFB29FBCF" box="[1107,1204,1044,1070]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="26">platyodon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
incluse) ont un rhizome dépourvu d’écailles mais couvert de poils multicellulaires, unisériés, raides, dressés, contigus, caractéristiques du genre 
<taxonomicName id="4C004D305E3CFFF7FAC3355DFA33FB8F" box="[1371,1454,1108,1134]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Dennstaedtiaceae" genus="Blotiella" kingdom="Plantae" order="Polypodiales" pageId="11" pageNumber="26" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B974EAA15E3CFFF7FAC3355DFA33FB8F" box="[1371,1454,1108,1134]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="26">Blotiella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EF914B425E3CFFF7FCAB357DFC5DFB6F" author="KRAMER K. U." box="[819,960,1140,1166]" pageId="11" pageNumber="26" pagination="88" refId="ref8969" refString="KRAMER K. U. 1990. - Blotiella, in KUBITZKI K. (ed.), Families and Genera of Vascular Plants, 1: Pteridophytes and Gymnosperms. Springer, Berlin: 88." type="book chapter" year="1990">Kramer 1990</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EF914B425E3CFFF7FC56357DFB1CFB6F" author="SMITH A. R. &amp; PRYER K. M. &amp; SCHUETTPELZ E. &amp; KORALL P. &amp; DER H. &amp; WOLF P. G." box="[974,1153,1140,1166]" pageId="11" pageNumber="26" refId="ref9870" refString="SMITH A. R., PRYER K. M., SCHUETTPELZ E., KORALL P., SCHNEI- DER H. &amp; WOLF P. G. 2008. - Fern classification, in RANKER T. A. AND HAUFLER C. H. (eds), Biology and Evolution of Ferns and Lycophytres. Cambridge University Press, Cambridge, 480 p." type="book" year="2008">
Smith 
<emphasis id="B974EAA15E3CFFF7FB88357CFBDFFB6F" box="[1040,1090,1140,1166]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="26">et al.</emphasis>
2008
</bibRefCitation>
). Le limbe des 
<taxonomicName id="4C004D305E3CFFF7FA8A357CFAD4FB6F" box="[1298,1353,1141,1166]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Pteridaceae" genus="Pteris" kingdom="Plantae" order="Polypodiales" pageId="11" pageNumber="26" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B974EAA15E3CFFF7FA8A357CFAD4FB6F" box="[1298,1353,1141,1166]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="26">Pteris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
est glabre à subglabre (
<bibRefCitation id="EF914B425E3CFFF7FC29359DFBEDFB4F" author="SMITH A. R. &amp; PRYER K. M. &amp; SCHUETTPELZ E. &amp; KORALL P. &amp; DER H. &amp; WOLF P. G." box="[945,1136,1172,1198]" pageId="11" pageNumber="26" refId="ref9870" refString="SMITH A. R., PRYER K. M., SCHUETTPELZ E., KORALL P., SCHNEI- DER H. &amp; WOLF P. G. 2008. - Fern classification, in RANKER T. A. AND HAUFLER C. H. (eds), Biology and Evolution of Ferns and Lycophytres. Cambridge University Press, Cambridge, 480 p." type="book" year="2008">
Smith 
<emphasis id="B974EAA15E3CFFF7FC66359CFBAFFB4F" box="[1022,1074,1172,1198]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="26">et al.</emphasis>
2008
</bibRefCitation>
); celui de 
<taxonomicName id="4C004D305E3CFFF7FB7E359CFA11FB4F" box="[1254,1420,1172,1198]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Pteridaceae" genus="Pteris" kingdom="Plantae" order="Polypodiales" pageId="11" pageNumber="26" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lanceifolia">
<emphasis id="B974EAA15E3CFFF7FB7E359CFA11FB4F" box="[1254,1420,1172,1198]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="26">Pteris lanceifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
est hirsute avec, sur le rachis, les costae et souvent la marge, des poils semblables à ceux du rhizome mais plus souples. 
<collectingRegion id="49C4F8515E3CFFF7FAD335DDFAF3FB0F" box="[1355,1390,1236,1262]" country="Cameroon" name="East" pageId="11" pageNumber="26">Les</collectingRegion>
spores des 
<taxonomicName id="4C004D305E3CFFF7FCCC35FDFC16FAEC" box="[852,907,1268,1293]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Pteridaceae" genus="Pteris" kingdom="Plantae" order="Polypodiales" pageId="11" pageNumber="26" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B974EAA15E3CFFF7FCCC35FDFC16FAEC" box="[852,907,1268,1293]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="26">Pteris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sont tétraédriques à globuleuses, trilètes (
<bibRefCitation id="EF914B425E3CFFF7FAAF35FAFCF8FACF" author="SMITH A. R. &amp; PRYER K. M. &amp; SCHUETTPELZ E. &amp; KORALL P. &amp; DER H. &amp; WOLF P. G." pageId="11" pageNumber="26" refId="ref9870" refString="SMITH A. R., PRYER K. M., SCHUETTPELZ E., KORALL P., SCHNEI- DER H. &amp; WOLF P. G. 2008. - Fern classification, in RANKER T. A. AND HAUFLER C. H. (eds), Biology and Evolution of Ferns and Lycophytres. Cambridge University Press, Cambridge, 480 p." type="book" year="2008">
Smith 
<emphasis id="B974EAA15E3CFFF7FAE635FDFA32FAEC" box="[1406,1455,1267,1293]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="26">et al.</emphasis>
2008
</bibRefCitation>
); celles des 
<taxonomicName id="4C004D305E3CFFF7FC43341AFB4FFACF" authority="(Kramer 1990)" baseAuthorityName="Kramer" baseAuthorityYear="1990" box="[987,1234,1299,1326]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Dennstaedtiaceae" genus="Blotiella" kingdom="Plantae" order="Polypodiales" pageId="11" pageNumber="26" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B974EAA15E3CFFF7FC43341AFBB3FACC" box="[987,1070,1299,1325]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="26">Blotiella</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EF914B425E3CFFF7FBA3341DFB57FACF" author="KRAMER K. U." box="[1083,1226,1300,1326]" pageId="11" pageNumber="26" pagination="88" refId="ref8969" refString="KRAMER K. U. 1990. - Blotiella, in KUBITZKI K. (ed.), Families and Genera of Vascular Plants, 1: Pteridophytes and Gymnosperms. Springer, Berlin: 88." type="book chapter" year="1990">Kramer 1990</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
et de 
<taxonomicName id="4C004D305E3CFFF7FA93341DFA33FACC" box="[1291,1454,1299,1325]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Pteridaceae" genus="Pteris" kingdom="Plantae" order="Polypodiales" pageId="11" pageNumber="26" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lanceifolia">
<emphasis id="B974EAA15E3CFFF7FA93341DFA33FACC" box="[1291,1454,1299,1325]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="26">Pteris lanceifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sont réniformes à ellipsoïdes, monolètes.Ces observations nous amènent à exclure 
<taxonomicName id="4C004D305E3CFFF7FC77345DFB6BFA8C" authority="J. Agardh" authorityName="J. Agardh" box="[1007,1270,1363,1389]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Pteridaceae" genus="Pteris" kingdom="Plantae" order="Polypodiales" pageId="11" pageNumber="26" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lanceifolia">
<emphasis id="B974EAA15E3CFFF7FC77345DFB0EFA8C" box="[1007,1171,1363,1389]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="26">Pteris lanceifolia</emphasis>
J.Agardh
</taxonomicName>
du genre 
<taxonomicName id="4C004D305E3CFFF7FAC6345DFA08FA8C" box="[1374,1429,1364,1389]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Pteridaceae" genus="Pteris" kingdom="Plantae" order="Polypodiales" pageId="11" pageNumber="26" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B974EAA15E3CFFF7FAC6345DFA08FA8C" box="[1374,1429,1364,1389]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="26">Pteris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
et à le placer dans le genre 
<taxonomicName id="4C004D305E3CFFF7FBBE347AFBE4FA6C" baseAuthorityName="Kramer" baseAuthorityYear="1990" box="[1062,1145,1395,1421]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Dennstaedtiaceae" genus="Blotiella" kingdom="Plantae" order="Polypodiales" pageId="11" pageNumber="26" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B974EAA15E3CFFF7FBBE347AFBE4FA6C" box="[1062,1145,1395,1421]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="26">Blotiella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
